= lesson 19: intermission 2

We are two thirds of the way through! Now you know 79 Toki Pona words, plus some
names.

Toki Pona isn't just a language people write stories in. Many people speak it
online, chatting with one another. To wrap up Part 2 of this course, let's try
to read a casual conversation:

TODO: port dialogue

There is still much to learn, but now you can hold a conversation, ask and
answer questions, and ask your partner to help you out. Toki Pona is most
pleasant when you have got someone to enjoy it together with. So go out into the
community, meet new people, make friends!

If you want to combine listening and talking, join a
[VRChat](https://bsky.app/profile/tokiponavr.bsky.social) meetup, where people
can hang out as virtual avatars! Every Saturday some Toki Pona speakers and
learners come to enjoy our time together, and talk about things we care about in
this nice language.
